{
  "texts": [
    "Participants very often knew about or actively searched for examples from papers that were related to their work.",
    "Another commonly used strategy was to use search engines (e.g., Google) or Q&A forums (e.g., Stack Overflow) for visual and code examples, and sometimes even additional recommendations by these tools: \"I think what happens at times is I really like Google's suggested images.",
    "I'll Google a figure that I'm kind of interested in and I'll see like related ones on the sidebar.\"",
    "Fig. 2:2Fig.",
    "2: Example circular condition probe for modification task (T5), showing prompts with example tasks (top) and technique thumbnails (bottom)."
  ]
}